					<description><![CDATA[<p>Funding Round Accelerates Private Market Innovation Mosaic has raised $18 million in Series A funding led by Radical Ventures. The round supports its ambition to modernise deal modelling across private</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/mosaic-raises-18m/" data-wpel-link="internal">Mosaic Raises $18M To Expand AI Deal Modelling Platform</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<h2><b>Funding Round Accelerates Private Market Innovation</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Mosaic has raised $18 million in Series A funding led by Radical Ventures. The round supports its ambition to modernise deal modelling across private markets. The company plans to expand product capabilities and enter adjacent sectors. These include investment banking and private </span><a href="https://www.emagia.com/resources/glossary/credit-workflow/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">credit workflows</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Private market firms rely heavily on spreadsheet models for deal analysis. These processes require hours of manual input and repeated adjustments. Errors in spreadsheets often create costly risks for investment teams. Mosaic aims to replace this workflow with structured and automated systems.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The platform combines deterministic calculations with AI-driven ingestion tools. This allows deal teams to complete analysis faster and with greater accuracy. It also reduces reliance on manual spreadsheet updates that slow decision making. The company believes this approach will reshape how firms evaluate investment opportunities.</span></p>
<h2><b>Platform Delivers Faster And More Reliable Deal Analysis</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Mosaic’s platform is already used by leading private market institutions. These include major private equity firms and global advisory groups. Users report significant improvements in workflow speed and accuracy. Core analyses such as leveraged buyouts and discounted cash flow models are completed much faster.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The platform removes common spreadsheet errors that affect financial models. It uses a rules-based engine to ensure consistent outputs across transactions. This helps teams standardise processes and build reliable internal systems. It also supports better collaboration across deal teams.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Mosaic Autopilot is a key feature within the platform. It allows users to generate models through a simple prompt. The system processes documents and produces a complete model within minutes. This reduces time spent on mechanical work and increases time for investment judgement.</span></p>
<h2><b>Expansion Into Investment Banking And Credit Markets<br />
</b></h2>
<div id="attachment_200249" style="width: 1322px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-200249" class="size-full wp-image-200249" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/a-cinematic-photograph-of-a-futuristic-d_SSc7XQdOTgaKvAPQAhkDzA_PHwXLGj0QTWo__7cfXA4BQ_hd.png" alt="AI-powered financial platform centralising deal data and automating analysis across investment banking and private credit workflows." width="1312" height="736" /><p id="caption-attachment-200249" class="wp-caption-text">Mosaic enables smarter investment decisions by centralising financial data, automating modelling, and uncovering insights from past deal performance. Source: Created by Ventureburn</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Mosaic plans to expand beyond private equity workflows. The company is targeting investment banks and private credit firms. These sectors face similar challenges with manual modelling and data processing. Automated systems can improve efficiency and reduce operational risk.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The platform also creates a centralised database for financial models. This allows firms to track historical deal data and compare assumptions. Over time, this builds institutional knowledge that improves decision quality. It also supports benchmarking against real outcomes.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company says this approach helps firms learn from past investments. It provides deeper insights into underwriting patterns and performance trends. This strengthens long-term strategy and reduces reliance on isolated models. It also enables more consistent evaluation across deals.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: <a href="https://ventureburn.com/c-infinity-raises-16m/" data-wpel-link="internal">C-Infinity Raises $16M To Scale AI Manufacturing Platform</a></span></p>
<h2><b>Growth Strategy Focuses On Scaling AI Across Finance</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Mosaic is growing its team to meet rising demand in more markets. They&#8217;re planning to bring on new people in engineering, product, and customer enablement. The goal? Make it easier to roll out their platform for big companies and help more users actually use it. They&#8217;re also working to boost their sales and presence in the market.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Their platform&#8217;s already catching on with some major firms. Several leading private equity groups have picked it as their modeling tool, and now investment banks are testing it for analyzing deals. Clearly, more financial players want to automate their workflows.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Mosaic says their system beats traditional tools by swapping scattered spreadsheets for organized, reliable models. That means faster work, fewer mistakes, and better decisions. The company wants to become the backbone for financial analysis.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">With new funding, Mosaic plans to keep building out its product and reach more markets. They&#8217;re also focused on making their AI smarter so it handles more types of work. All this puts Mosaic on track to become a major force in financial technology.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">To stay updated on crypto venture capital funding and market trends, visit our </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/category/news/venture-capital/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">venture capital news section</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> for more insights.</span></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/mosaic-raises-18m/" data-wpel-link="internal">Mosaic Raises $18M To Expand AI Deal Modelling Platform</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
